<Layout title="About">
  <h1>About</h1>

  <p>
    I'm Atheerium — a domain investor, freelance web developer, and solo builder based in
    Aflou, Algeria. I build tools, flip domains, and write about what I learn along the way.
  </p>

  <h2>what I do</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Domain investing</strong> — acquiring and selling premium .com domains. Portfolio includes names like FedZip.com, ChipWe.com, BusPin.com, and more.</li>
    <li><strong>Freelance development</strong> — building Next.js, Supabase, and Flutter applications for Gulf-region SMBs. Specializing in local payment integration (Tap, PayTabs, Mada) and bilingual Arabic/English interfaces.</li>
    <li><strong>Tool building</strong> — creating open-source tools for domain analysis, lead generation, and workflow automation.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>this site</h2>

  <p>
    Built with Astro, deployed on GitHub Pages. Markdown-first, no database, no comments,
    no JavaScript framework. Content lives in markdown files organized by category.
  </p>

  <p>
    Think of it as a public knowledge base — articles I've written, research I've done,
    projects I've built, and notes I've collected.
  </p>

